request.description:
This route allows a user to simulate a login interface. It uses a personal firebase key to get the information. In the body, the user must provide:

- Email
- Password
- returnSecureToken as true


It will return a token like the following:

``` json
{
    "idToken": "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6ImY1NWU0ZDkxOGE0ODY0YWQxMzUxMDViYmRjMDEwYWY5Njc5YzM0MTMiLCJ0eXAiOiJKV1QifQ..hvXRi89FOtD0eAMaJzh4ayw5dzH6Z9b5ioU4VwfIDYxrXBjUhUnuR2wVXoNBogToJzLqIrHV2pK416vFBfKCnD4XwgROlvc6Y3gUGeNQH2W_3zHGGkAiWd5qaTRfqcKPhbqocrAzw26hmXYuVHllwOwIxNUqjojDclj7rnN8okKZBKByi-rG8sVSTe2sN2wcsl-h6YY8iXxP-V350a3NxYQSB2aQOPRgisY8L5ym81igHgmE6B8ocyA2gf-e4J3A05zREmp0p_bAtoJkOHMhOFy75_AmqAGQ2qcP91FJzjN5nUDDVr0PkLMNbMhBBk_-n8u8KewqSoZTv0GCUwaOuA"
}

```

Once you get the token, the user has to copy & paste it as a bearer token in all routes required.

**This route only return a token if the user already exists, if not the user will see an error like the following:**

``` json
{
    "error": {
        "code": 400,
        "message": "EMAIL_NOT_FOUND",
        "errors": [
            {
                "message": "EMAIL_NOT_FOUND",
                "domain": "global",
                "reason": "invalid"
            }
        ]
    }
}

```

